    "attributes": {
        "action": "Investigation into Legal Expenses Insurance sold by Building Societies and Banks",
        "additional_details": "Many customers making legitimate claims find that the legal protection insurance sold to them is on a No Win No Fee basis and is not fit for purpose.\r\n\r\nThe scope of the inquiry should include but not limited to:\r\n \r\n- Complaints from 1980 onwards\r\n- The connection between Legal Expenses Insurance providers and the solicitors that they use\r\n- How the LEI provider, handles & manages each claim at every stage and legal costs\r\n- The use of experts, surveyors & structural engineers engaged in claims and the connection to the LEI provider\r\n- The instructions given to experts\r\n- The number of claims that have been rejected\r\n \r\nThe inquiry should determine the truth & accountability.",
        "background": "The Government should conduct a full Public Inquiry into Building Societies, Banks, Brokers & LEI Insurers selling of Legal Expenses Insurance (LEI) as add on policies from 1980. ",
